## Invalidation Criteria

### Bull Case (Consumer Resilience) Invalidation Thresholds

If the following occur **simultaneously for 3+ months**, the bearish consumer thesis is invalidated:

âœ… **Personal Saving Rate** rises above **6.0%** (buffer rebuilding)
âœ… **Credit Card Delinquency** drops below **2.5%** (stress fading)
âœ… **Real PCE YoY%** exceeds **3.0%** (acceleration)
âœ… **CB Expectations** exceeds **90** (optimism returning)
âœ… **Real DPI YoY%** exceeds **2.5%** (income growth supporting spending)
âœ… **CCI** exceeds **+0.5** (healthy regime)

**Action if Invalidated:** Rotate to **consumer discretionary** (XLY), **travel/leisure** (PEJ), **retail** (XRT). Consumer strength = cyclical outperformance.

---

### Bear Case (Consumer Collapse) Confirmation Thresholds

If the following occur, consumer is **deteriorating beyond fatigued into crisis**:

ðŸ”´ **Real PCE YoY%** turns **negative** (spending contraction)
ðŸ”´ **Personal Saving Rate** drops below **3.0%** (desperation)
ðŸ”´ **Credit Card Delinquency** exceeds **4.5%** (credit crisis)
ðŸ”´ **CB Expectations** drops below **65** (deep pessimism)
ðŸ”´ **Retail Sales 3M Avg** turns **negative** (demand destruction)
ðŸ”´ **CCI** drops below **-1.0** (crisis regime)

**Action if Confirmed:** Maximum defensive. Overweight **consumer staples** (XLP), **discount retail** (WMT, COST, DG), **utilities** (XLU). Avoid all discretionary exposure.

